ple, almonds, psyllium husks, pepper and remaining ½ tsp salt and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 5<b>."},{"content":"Add reserved buckwheat mixture and mix <b>5 sec\/\/speed 4<b>. Roll tablespoonfuls of the stuffing mixture into balls (approx. 30 balls in total) and place onto prepared baking tray. Bake for 25 minutes (180°C). Serve as desired (see Tips)."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Please refer to Mushroom stock paste recipe on this recipe chip or The Basic Cookbook for the Vegetable stock paste recipe.","If you have a second mixing bowl, simply set it aside with the buckwheat to let it soak and proceed with recipe using your second mixing bowl.","To save time, you can transfer the stuffing mixture into an oiled baking dish (20 cm), then decorate with fresh sage leaves, spray with oil and bake as per recipe.","We recommend serving this stuffing alongside roasted vegetables, potatoes and gravy."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","1h 10m","6 portions"]}